President Donald J. Trump spoke to NASA astronauts Christa Koch and Jessica Meir during the first all-woman spacewalk from the International Space Station (ISS). The President has put a renewed focus on space and human space exploration since taking office. He charged NASA with returning Americans to the Moon by 2024. This spacewalk highlights the advancements of women in science, technology, engineering, and mathematics (STEM), which is an initiative championed by both the President and Ivanka Trump. The Trump Administration has prioritized access to STEM education and has developed a strategy to build strong foundations for STEM literacy, increase diversity and inclusion in STEM, and prepare the STEM workforce for the future.